data.description: A Must See! Darling 2+ bedroom home on a quaint street near the heartbeat of downtown Rockport. This classic wood shingled home built in 1943 boasts a handsome cut granite foundation, skylights, a propane fire place, 4 y.o. roof, efficient Harvey windows, skylights, ceiling fans & hardwood floors. The 2 bedrooms on the first floor offer convenience for the ease of single floor living. Retreat to the 2nd floor, oversized & sunny with a 1/2 bath; a perfect fit for guests, or a home office, art space. Deep closets & storage galore! You will adore the established perennial gardens with sequential blooming & a private cobblestone patio for outdoor entertaining. Interior access to the basement with heat offers loads of sunlight, storage & a separate room for on-going projects. 2 exits to the outside lends itself to overhead storage protecting your kayak & garden tools from the elements. Relish in Rockport at the Beaches, Bearskin Neck, Eateries, Galleries &The Shalin Liu Performance Center.
